ion about the extent of preparation or resources allocated specifically for teacher training in the transcript.&#10;&#10;It is important to note that while the education sector is represented in the implementation group, it does not necessarily mean that every individual teacher is prepared or involved in the process. The preparation and awareness campaign's success will likely depend on how effectively the information and training are cascaded down to all teachers and school staff. Additionally, there may be a transition period during which teachers become more comfortable with the new legislation and its implications for their professional responsibilities.">
