lans to extend its scope to cover up to 18 years old. This extension recognizes that the issues faced by parents of older children may be different and require tailored advice and support.&#10;&#10;The Government is also conducting a mapping exercise to identify gaps or opportunities for more support, particularly in terms of providing positive alternatives to physical punishment and online resources for parents. They recognize that many parents use various methods, including the internet, to access information and seek help. This mapping exercise will enable them to create targeted interventions and ensure comprehensive support is available for parents throughout Wales.&#10;&#10;Lastly, the Welsh Government encourages universal services provided by local government, health, education, social services, social justice, and the third sector to help support parents and pass on information about positive alternatives to physical punishment. More targeted supports such as Flying Start and Families First also offer help and advice for parents in need.">
