on but emphasizes the importance of working closely with social services and collecting relevant data to monitor changes after the Bill's implementation. Overall, while there may be potential workload increases, professionals are prepared and believe they have adequate resources to support the Bill's implementation without lowering the threshold for significant harm or changing child protection procedures significantly.">
