    <edge source="The question is asking about confidence in the allocated budget of £2.2 million over six years for the organ donation awareness campaign, compared to previously spent amounts such as the £4 million for a similar campaign.&#10;&#10;Karen Cornish, the representative from the Welsh government, stated that they are &quot;as confident as we can be at this moment in time&quot; about the allocated budget being sufficient. However, she also mentioned working with focus groups and others to determine messaging needs, suggesting there may still be some uncertainty or ongoing planning efforts related to the campaign's budget.&#10;&#10;Lynne Neagle AM pointed out a disparity between the previously spent £4 million for an awareness campaign and the current allocation of £2.2 million over six years. She questioned whether this amount would be enough, especially considering that reaching various groups, including hard-to-reach ones, is necessary for such campaigns.&#10;&#10;Overall, while Karen Cornish expressed confidence in the allocated budget, there are concerns about whether it will be sufficient compared to previously spent amounts and taking into consideration the need to reach diverse audiences." target=" five years [correction: £2.2 million over six years]—is going to be enough? From memory, with the organ donation Bill, the amount was something in the region of around £7 million that was set aside, I think. Or maybe I'm misremembering that, but—&#10;Speaker: Karen Cornish&#10;Content: I think it was about £4 million—&#10;Speaker: Lynne Neagle AM&#10;Content: £4 million—&#10;Speaker: Karen Cornish&#10;Content: Something like that.&#10;Speaker: Lynne Neagle AM&#10;Content: So, there's a disparity, then. That was a few years ago. You've got to reach a lot of people, haven't you, with this, including some pretty hard-to-reach groups as well. Are you confident that amount of money is going to be enough?&#10;Speaker: Karen Cornish&#10;Content: We are as confident as we can be at this moment in time. We are obviously going to be working with focus groups and others to look at what sorts of messaging there will need to be. But in terms of the initial stages of the awareness campaign, we are, as I say, as confident as we can be,">
