re on public services, the legislative area is considered to be a continuation of existing work rather than a new category.&#10;&#10;Based on this information, social services do not anticipate a significant change in intervention thresholds if they receive more reports about instances of physical punishment towards children following the possible change in law. They are prepared for potential workload increases and believe that existing resources can manage any additional referrals. Social work professionals also expect awareness-raising campaigns to lead to a decrease in physical punishment incidents over time.">
